<p id="comment-truncated-5247-949918115" class="comment">
Well, maybe the word 'revenge' is a little, shall we say, strong. This corner will include several motives under the umbrella word in the title. The following goes more under the heading of expose and apology. After you are done at this website go to...
</p>
<p id="comment-full-5247-949918115" class="comment" style="display: none">
Well, maybe the word 'revenge' is a little, shall we say, strong. This corner will include several motives under the umbrella word in the title. The following goes more under the heading of expose and apology. After you are done at this website go to wikipedia.com and type Congressman Andrew J. May into the search box, or google May+Garsson. At Wikipedia article scroll down to Munitions Scandal, and articles sited below in biblio. It is an article about perhaps the first war profiteering scandal publicized across the nation. It is about my Grandfather, Murray Garsson, my granduncle, Henry Garsson, and my father Joseph Garsson in relation to Congressman May. It is about a large-scale scamming of the American Taxpayer and the U.S. government to the tune of millions of dollars. Even worse, it gave birth to an entire system of war and monkey business as usual, from Contragate to Blackwatergate non-construction in Iraq, with billions at stake these days. These people, my relatives, may as well have written the book &quot;How to Bilk the Government Out of Billions, for Dummies.&quot; My father, then in his twenties was kept out of the army during WWII so that he could work for these three crooks. All were eventually indicted and tried and convicted, with the exception of my father. An expert skier, he was instead recruited into the Ski Brigade, utilized for various purposes to cross the Alps from Switzerland into Italy. Better a war hero, however unwilling, than to go to jail. Bully for him, it's about the only heroic act of his life. Worse than the millions, they were at least in part responsible for the malfunctioning of defective fuses manufactured under their less than watchful eyes, the resultant explosian killed thirty-eight American soldiers. My writing of this here is not about revenge, as my father died last year, he cannot know I've written this. What this is about is my sincere wish, however belatedly, knowing I am in no way responsible, I was not born at the time, to say: I'm sorry. I apologize to the spirits of the soldiers who died, I apologize to their families, their friends, and to the American people, and the government at the time. Like I said, I wasn't to be born for many years to come, it is said in Judeo Christian society that the sins of the fathers shall not be visited upon the children. But they are, aren't they? When we know what happened, when we are enough in touch with our human feelings to know how we feel, when we are people of honor, of course it hurts to know, and to know that these are the people who gave us birth and raised us... so to speak. my mother thought it was swell to be around these criminals associated with gangsters (read the Time and Newsweek articles). There is no question that the engineers of munitions disasters do not know how to run a marriage, or how to treat their children. How about some population control, Lord knows the world could use a lot of that. Why not begin with a program of forbidding criminals from having children?   
</p>
